-------------------------------------------------------------------
Wed Jun 17 16:41:59 UTC 2026 - Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>

- Initial package (version 0.25.4): the falcosecurity libs (libscap
  and libsinsp) built as shared libraries
- Enable the inspector thread pool (ENABLE_THREAD_POOL) using the
  system bshoshany-thread-pool
- Run the libsinsp gtest unit-test suite (844 tests) during %%check
- Ship the libscap test_input engine: with CREATE_TEST_TARGETS libsinsp
  links it (DT_NEEDED), so libsinsp0 needs it at runtime
- Restrict to the arches whose modern-BPF vmlinux.h is vendored
  (x86_64 aarch64 ppc64le s390x)
- Trim BuildRequires to the set the build actually uses (drop unused
  grpc/protobuf/libcurl/libcares/openssl/luajit/ncurses/yaml-cpp/
  libb64/libjq) and drop cmake flags that are not real options in
  this release
